{{short description|American actress and singer}} {{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}} {{Infobox person | name = Chloe Bennet | image = Chloe Bennet by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg | caption = Bennet at the 2018 [[Wondercon]] | birth_name = Chloe Wang | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|04|18}} | birth_place = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S. | module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes|c={{linktext|汪|可|盈}}<ref name=qq20130823>{{cite web |url=http://ent.qq.com/a/20130823/009941.htm |title="Shén dùn jú" gōngbù zhǔjiǎo zàoxíng zhào wāngkěyíng shìyǎn hēikè sī kǎi|script-title=zh:《神盾局》公布主角造型照 汪可盈饰演黑客斯凯 |publisher=QQ.com |date=August 23, 2013 |agency=Tencent Entertainment News |accessdate=August 29, 2013 |language=Chinese|trans-title='SHIELD' announced; Wang Keying plays hacker Skye |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131013180335/http://ent.qq.com/a/20130823/009941.htm#p=1 |archivedate=October 13, 2013 |deadurl=no}} ({{Google translation|en|zh|http://ent.qq.com/a/20130823/009941.htm}})</ref><ref name=baidu>{{cite web |url=http://baike.baidu.com/view/2411930.htm|script-title=zh:汪可盈 |publisher=[[Baidu]] |accessdate=August 29, 2013 |language=Chinese|trans-title=Wang Keying|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130829232658/http://baike.baidu.com/view/2411930.htm|archive-date=August 29, 2013|dead-url=Yes |df=}} ({{Google translation|en|zh|http://baike.baidu.com/view/2411930.htm}})</ref><!--does not appear archivable by Archive.org or Webcitation.org. Archived at , an archive disallowed as a reference source and included here in broken form only as a last resort if Baidu page goes dead--><!--Superseded by "Wikipedia:Archive.is RFC 4"-->|p=Wāng Kěyíng}} | occupation = Actress, singer | years_active = 2010–present }}
'''Chloe Wang''' (born April 18, 1992), known professionally as '''Chloe Bennet''', is an American actress and singer. She is known for her role as [[Daisy Johnson|Daisy "Skye" Johnson / Quake]] on the television series ''[[Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' (2013–present) and the animated series ''[[Marvel Rising: Secret Warriors]]''.
==Early life== Chloe Bennet was born Chloe Wang on April 18, 1992, in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]].<ref name=tvg>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/chloe-bennet/bio/555803 |title=Chloe Bennet |work=[[TV Guide]] |accessdate=September 30, 2015 |archivedate=September 27, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140927094410/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/chloe-bennet/bio/555803 |deadurl=yes<!-- Do not set to no, as the birthdate is only supported by the archived version-->}}</ref> She is the daughter of Bennet Wang,<ref name="profile">{{cite news |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-12-09/entertainment/chi-chloe-bennet-profile-20131209_1_chloe-bennet-grant-ward-agent-phil-Coulson |title=Chloe Bennet brings humor and heart to 'Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.' |date=December 9, 2013 |first=Courtney |last=Crowder |work=[[Chicago Tribune]] |accessdate=September 30, 2015 |archivedate=July 7, 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707061137/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2013-12-09/entertainment/chi-chloe-bennet-profile-20131209_1_chloe-bennet-grant-ward-agent-phil-coulson |deadurl=no}}</ref> an investment banker,<ref name= Hiltbrand/> and Stephanie Crane, an [[internist]].{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}
Bennet's father is [[Han Chinese]] and her mother is Caucasian.<ref name=wong2014>{{cite news |last=Wong |first=Tony |title=Actress Chloe Bennet says changing her name changed her luck |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/television/2014/05/11/actress_chloe_bennet_says_changing_her_name_changed_her_luck.html# |accessdate=May 12, 2014 |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] |date=May 11, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022031153/http://www.thestar.com/entertainment/television/2014/05/11/actress_chloe_bennet_says_changing_her_name_changed_her_luck.html%23 |archivedate=October 22, 2014 |deadurl=no |df=}}</ref> She has six brothers: three biological, two foster and one adopted; two are [[African American]] and one is [[Mexican-Filipino]].<ref name="profile"/> She attended [[St. Ignatius College Prep]].<ref name="profile"/>
==Singing career== In 2007, at age 15, Bennet moved to [[China]] to pursue a singing career<ref name=Hiltbrand/> under her birthname, Chloe Wang ({{linktext|汪|可|盈|lang=zh}}).{{r|baidu}} While in China, Bennet lived with her paternal grandmother in [[Beijing]],{{r|tvg}} and studied [[Standard Mandarin|Mandarin]].<ref name= Hiltbrand>{{cite web |last=Hiltbrand |first=David |date=November 12, 2013 |title=Chloe Bennet out to impress the guys |url=http://www.philly.com/philly/columnists/david_hiltbrand/20131112_Chloe_Bennet_out_to_impress_the_guys.html |newspaper=[[Philadelphia Inquirer]] |accessdate=May 12, 2014 |archivedate=December 18, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141218191115/http://www.philly.com/philly/columnists/david_hiltbrand/20131112_Chloe_Bennet_out_to_impress_the_guys.html |deadurl=no}}</ref> She released two singles, both in 2011: "Uh Oh" and "Every Day in Between".<ref name="iTunes">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/chlo%C3%A9-wang/424625368 |title=Chloé Wang on Apple Music |website=[[iTunes Store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]] |accessdate=May 5, 2018}}</ref>
==Acting career== [[File:Chloe Bennet at PaleyFest 2014.jpg|thumb|150px|Bennet at [[PaleyFest]] 2014]] In 2010 she moved to [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref name=Hiltbrand/> Her first on-screen appearance was as a host for the short-lived [[TeenNick]] summer dance series ''[[The Nightlife]]''. She appeared in the 2011 music video for [[South Korea]]n band [[Big Bang (South Korean band)|BIGBANG]]'s "[[Tonight (Big Bang EP)|Tonight]]".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2011/03/chloe-wang-poses-for-selcas-with-big-bang-members |title="Tonight" actress Chloe Wang poses for selcas with Big Bang members |publisher=[[Allkpop]] |date=March 3, 2011|access-date=May 26, 2017}}</ref>
While pursuing an acting career in Hollywood, she changed her name to "Chloe Bennet", after having trouble booking gigs with her last name. According to Bennet, using her real name rather than his last name avoids difficulties being cast as an ethnic [[Asian American]] while respecting her father.<ref name=wong2014/><ref name="NPR 2017"/>
From 2012 to 2013, she had a recurring supporting role in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] drama series ''[[Nashville (2012 TV series)|Nashville]]'' as Hailey.<ref name=hp/> In December 2012, she was cast as a series regular on the ABC series ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'',<ref name=hp>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/joss-whedons-shield-nashville-chloe-bennet-405087 |title=Joss Whedon's 'S.H.I.E.L.D.' Pilot Enlists 'Nashville' Actress (Exclusive) |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=December 19, 2012 |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710005848/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/joss-whedons-shield-nashville-chloe-bennet-405087 |archivedate=July 10, 2015 |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|url=http://tvline.com/2012/12/19/joss-whedon-shield-pilot-cast-chloe-bennet/ |title=Joss Whedon's S.H.I.E.L.D. Pilot Completes Casting With Nashville Actress |publisher=[[TVLine]] |date=December 19, 2012 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121221012247/http://tvline.com/2012/12/19/joss-whedon-shield-pilot-cast-chloe-bennet/ |archivedate=December 21, 2012 |accessdate=May 5, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gallagher|first=Brian|url=http://www.movieweb.com/news/marvels-s-h-i-e-l-d-adds-chloe-bennett-as-skye |title=Marvel's S.H.I.E.L.D. Adds Chloe Bennett as Skye |website=[[MovieWeb]] |date=December 19, 2012 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130220162200/http://www.movieweb.com/news/marvels-s-h-i-e-l-d-adds-chloe-bennett-as-skye |archivedate=February 20, 2013 |accessdate=May 5, 2018}}</ref> which premiered on September 24, 2013, where she portrays the character [[Daisy Johnson|Daisy "Skye" Johnson / Quake]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Abrams|first=Natalie|url=http://ew.com/article/2014/12/10/agents-shield-skye-daisy-johnson-quake-inhuman/ |title='Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.' reveals Skye's true identity – what's next? |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=December 10, 2014|accessdate=May 5, 2018}}</ref>
In 2017 she was cast in a musical remake of the 1983 film ''[[Valley Girl (film)#Remake|Valley Girl]]'' as Karen, the "Queen Bee".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/chloe-bennett-logan-paul-jessie-ennis-ashleigh-murray-valley-girl-mgm-1202077104/ |title='Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Chloe Bennet, Logan Paul & More Join MGM's 'Valley Girl' Remake |last=N'Duka |first=Amanda |date=April 25, 2017 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=May 8, 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170501081846/http://deadline.com/2017/04/chloe-bennett-logan-paul-jessie-ennis-ashleigh-murray-valley-girl-mgm-1202077104/ |archivedate=May 1, 2017 |df=}}</ref> The film was scheduled for release in June 2018, but has been postponed due to controversy around one of its cast members, [[Logan Paul]].<ref>{{cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|url=http://deadline.com/2018/03/logan-paul-valley-girl-release-date-change-1202307858/|title='Valley Girl' Remake With Controversial YouTuber Logan Paul Looking For Another Release Date|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 1, 2018|accessdate=May 5, 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== In 2018, she revealed that she has been struggling with [[anxiety]] and [[ADHD]] since childhood.<ref>{{cite web|last= Douglas|first=Esme|url=https://childmind.org/blog/chloe-bennet-myyoungerself/|title=Chloe Bennet - My younger self|work=Childmind institute|date=2018|accessdate=July 27, 2018}}</ref> From July to October 2018, Bennet was in a relationship with YouTube personality [[Logan Paul]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/chloe-bennet-and-logan-paul-split/|title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Chloe Bennet and YouTuber Logan Paul Split|last1=Chiu|first1=Melody|last2=Stone|first2=Natalie|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=October 16, 2018|accessdate=October 19, 2018}}</ref>
==Views== {{Quote box |quote="I think what's really dangerous with what, continuously, is happening with Asian-Americans in Hollywood is there's a narrative that white Hollywood, or just any other ethnicity really in Hollywood gives to Asian-Americans that, 'You're the butt of the joke.' They're determining that we're the nerds, that we're the shy girls or that the guy that can't be sexy because he's an Asian man." | source = —Bennet in a September 2017 interview for [[NPR]]<ref name="NPR 2017">{{cite web|last=Martin|first=Michel|date=September 3, 2017|url=https://www.npr.org/2017/09/03/548296823/actress-chloe-bennet-wants-to-change-the-narrative-for-asian-americans-in-hollyw|title=Actress Chloe Bennet Wants To Change The Narrative For Asian-Americans In Hollywood|publisher=[[NPR]]|accessdate=May 5, 2018}}</ref> | width = 35em | align = right}} Bennet has described the American film and television industry as racist against Asians. In a 2016 interview, she noted, "Oh, the first audition I went on after I changed my name [from Wang to Bennet], I got booked. So that's a pretty clear little snippet of how Hollywood works."<ref name="changed her">{{cite web |last=Tharp |first=Sharon |date=September 1, 2017 |url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/chloe-bennet-changed-her-name-because-hollywood-racism-w500747 |title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D's Chloe Bennet Changed Her Last Name Because 'Hollywood Is Racist' |work=[[Us Weekly]]|accessdate=May 5, 2018}}</ref>
In September 2017, after actor [[Ed Skrein]] stepped down from his role as Major Ben Daimio in the then-in production film ''[[Hellboy (2019 film)|Hellboy]]'' following backlash over the fact that Skrein, a white man, was playing Daimio, a character who is [[Japanese-American]] in the ''[[Hellboy]]'' comics, Bennet wrote a since-deleted post on [[Instagram]] in which she applauded Skrein's decision, and addressed her own experiences as an Asian actor in Hollywood, saying, "Changing my last name doesn't change the fact that my BLOOD is half Chinese, that I lived in China, speak Mandarin or that I was culturally raised both American and Chinese. It means I had to pay my rent, and Hollywood is racist and wouldn't cast me with a last name that made them uncomfortable."<ref name="changed her" />
