| <!-- Sport --> | country = {{RSA}} | sport = sprint runner and long jumper | position = | disability = | disability_class = T38 | event = | event_type = | collegeteam = | universityteam = | league = | league_type = | club = | team = | turnedpro = | turnedpro_type = | partner = | former_partner = | coach = | retired = | coaching = | module2 = | <!-- Achievements and titles --> | worlds = | regionals = | nationals = | olympics = | paralympics = | commonwealth = | highestranking = | pb = 49.46 | <!-- Medal record --> | show-medals = | medaltemplates = {{MedalSport | [[Track and field]] (athletics)}} {{MedalCountry|{{RSA}}}} {{MedalCompetition|[[Paralympic Games]]}} {{MedalGold| [[2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio de Janeiro]] | [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Paralympics – Men's 400 metres T38|Men's 400m T38]]}} {{MedalSilver| [[2012 Summer Paralympics|2012 London]] | [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Paralympics – Men's 100 metres T38|Men's 100m T38]]}} {{MedalSilver| [[2012 Summer Paralympics|2012 London]] | [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Paralympics – Men's 200 metres T38|Men's 200m T38]]}} {{MedalBronze| [[2012 Summer Paralympics|2012 London]] | [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Paralympics – Men's long jump#F37-38|Long jump F37-38]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[IPC Athletics World Championships|IPC World Championships]]}} {{MedalSilver|[[2013 IPC Athletics World Championships|2013 Lyon]]|[[2013 IPC Athletics World Championships – Men's 100 metres|Men's 100m - T38]]}} {{MedalSilver|[[2013 IPC Athletics World Championships|2013 Lyon]]|[[2013 IPC Athletics World Championships – Men's 200 metres|Men's 200m - T38]]}} {{MedalSilver|[[2015 IPC Athletics World Championships|2015 Doha]]|[[2015 IPC Athletics World Championships – Men's 200 metres|Men's 200m - T38]]}} {{MedalSilver|[[2015 IPC Athletics World Championships|2015 Doha]]|[[2015 IPC Athletics World Championships – Men's long jump|Men's long jump - T38]]}} }}
'''Dyan Buis''' (born 30 November 1990 in [[Riversdale, Western Cape]]) is a South African Paralympic sprint runner and long jumper. He has mild cerebral palsy and competes in the [[T38 (classification)|T38]] class.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.paralympic.org/Athletes/Biographies|publisher=IPC|title=Dyan Buis|accessdate=6 September 2012}}</ref>
In 2012 Buis was a student at [[Global University]] in Cape Town, RSA, in Religious and Theological Studies, and trained at Maties Helderberg Disabled Sports Club in Stellenbosch. He competed at the [[2012 Paralympic Games]], where he won a Bronze Medal in the men's long jump with a world record time for his class of 6.48 metres. He also won a Silver Medal in the Men's 100m for his class.
In 2016 at the 2016 Paralympics, Buis ran a 54.66 in the second heat to qualify third for the finals behind Dixon de Jesus Hooker Velasquez and Weiner Javier Diaz Mosquera both from Colombia. In the Finals, Buis exploded out of the blocks and ran his Personal Best 49.46 seconds to claim Gold. The second place went to China's Jianwen Hu and Third to Colombia's Weiner Javier Diaz Mosquera<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.necn.com/09/05/12/PARA-SA-LD-WRAP-by-Jenny-Bernstein/landing_nation.html?&apID=fdf48ede0d25447681df2b21d8415755|title=PARA-SA-LD-WRAP|author=Bernstein, Jenny|accessdate=7 September 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130130032606/http://www.necn.com/09/05/12/PARA-SA-LD-WRAP-by-Jenny-Bernstein/landing_nation.html?&apID=fdf48ede0d25447681df2b21d8415755|archivedate=30 January 2013|df=}}</ref>
