'''Pance F. Pondaag''' (February 18, 1951 – June 3, 2010) was an [[Indonesia]]n [[pop singer]] and [[songwriter]]. The ''[[Jakarta Post]]'' described Pondaag as one of Indonesia's most famous pop singers during the 1980s.<ref name=jp>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Singer Pance Pondaag dies at 59|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/06/03/singer-pance-pondaag-dies-59.html|work=[[Jakarta Post]]|publisher=|date=2010-06-24|accessdate=2010-06-03|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100605083746/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/06/03/singer-pance-pondaag-dies-59.html|archivedate=2010-06-05|df=}}</ref>
Pondaag was born on February 18, 1951, in [[Makassar]], [[Sulawesi]]. Pance Pondaag died of a stroke at his home in [[Pluit]], [[North Jakarta]], at 5 p.m. on June 3, 2010, at the age of 59.<ref name=jp/> He was from the [[Minahasa]] and [[Sangirese people|Sangirese]] ethnic group.
