{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox Officeholder |name = Prof. Tamo Mibang |image = |imagesize = |caption = |order = |office = [[Vice-Chancellor]] of [[Rajiv Gandhi University]]<ref name="Arunachal needs a library movement: Prof. Tamo Mibang">{{cite news|last1=Mibang|first1=Tamo|title=Tamo|url=http://www.arunachaltimes.in/wordpress/2013/04/06/arunachal-needs-a-library-movement-prof-tamo-mibang/|accessdate=24 November 2014|publisher=The Arunachal Times|date=5 April 2013}}</ref> |term_start = |term_end = |predecessor = |successor = |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |alma_mater = |profession =[[Professor]] |religion =[[Donyi-Polo]] |}}
'''Prof. Tamo Mibang''' is the [[Vice Chancellor]] of [[Rajiv Gandhi University]] in [[Doimukh]], [[Arunachal Pradesh]], [[India]].<ref>Prof. Tamo Mibang appointed as Vice Chancellor of [[Rajiv Gandhi University]] [http://www.edu-leaders.com/edu/news/14516/tamo-mibang-appointed-vc-rajiv-gandhi-university], ''The Edu Leaders'', 2011</ref> He is from the [[Adi people|Adi Tribe]] of [[Arunachal Pradesh]].<ref>[http://www.arunachaltimes.in/wordpress/2013/04/06/arunachal-needs-a-library-movement-prof-tamo-mibang/ "Arunachal needs a library movement: Prof. Tamo Mibang"], ''The Arunachal Times'', 5 April 2013</ref> ==Bibliography== This is an incomplete list of his books. *''[[Social Change in Arunachal Pradesh]]''<ref name="Mibang1994">{{cite book|author=Tamo Mibang|title=Social Change in Arunachal Pradesh: The Minyongs, 1947-1981|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B3eIAAAACAAJ|year=1994|publisher=Omsons Publication|isbn=978-81-7117-130-9|page=Cover}}</ref> *''[[Tribal Studies - Emerging Frontiers of Knowledge (book)|Tribal Studies - Emerging Frontiers of Knowledge]]''<ref name="Mibang2007">{{cite book|author=Tamo Mibang|title=Tribal Studies - Emerging Frontiers of Knowledge|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6FFHggw8rGgC|year=2007|publisher=Mittal Publications|isbn=978-81-8324-215-8}}</ref> *''An introduction to Adi language''<ref name="MibangAbraham2001">{{cite book|author1=Tamo Mibang|author2=P. T. Abraham|title=An introduction to Adi language|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kCdkAAAAMAAJ|year=2001|publisher=Himalayan Publishers|isbn=978-81-86393-35-2|page=1}}</ref> *''Tribal Villages in Arunachal Pradesh''<ref name="MibangBehera2004">{{cite book|author1=Tamo Mibang|author2=M. C. Behera|title=Tribal Villages in Arunachal Pradesh: Changing Human Interface|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kWPnPQAACAAJ|year=2004|publisher=Abhijeet Publications|isbn=978-81-88683-41-3|page=1}}</ref> *''Marriage in tribal societies'''<ref name="MibangBehera2007">{{cite book|a